{{Use British English|date=July 2015}} {{Infobox book | italic title = <!--(see above)--> | name = No Man's Land: An Investigative Journey Through Kenya and Tanzania | image = File:No Man's Land (first edition).JPG | image_size = 200px | alt = | caption = | author = [[George Monbiot]] | audio_read_by = | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = United Kingdom | language = English | series = | release_number = | subject = [[Tanzania]], [[Kenya]], inequality | set_in = | published = [[London]] | publisher = Macmillan | publisher2 = Green Books | pub_date = 1994 | media_type = Print | pages = | awards = | isbn = 1903998263 | oclc = | dewey = | congress = | preceded_by = | followed_by = | native_wikisource = | wikisource = | notes = | exclude_cover = | website = }}
'''''No Man's Land: An Investigative Journey Through Kenya and Tanzania''''' is a 1994 book by [[British people|British]] writer and environmental and political activist, [[George Monbiot]]. Another edition was released in 2003.
==Background== The book details Monbiot's travels through [[Kenya]] and [[Tanzania]], the inequality and harsh conditions he witnesses, along with the natural beauty he observes.
==Reception== ''No Man's Land'' was praised by diverse sources, from [[Niall Ferguson]] in the ''[[Daily Mail]]'', [[Oliver Tickell]] in the ''[[Daily Telegraph]] and in ''Africa Analysis'', where it was described as 'An inquiring book by a sensitive man'.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.newsfromnowhere.org.uk/books/DisplayBookInfo.php?ISBN=9781903998267 |title=No Man's Land: An Investigative Journey Through Kenya and Tanzania by George Monbiot - News From Nowhere Radical & Community Bookshop, Liverpool |website=Newsfromnowhere.org.uk |date= |accessdate=2016-10-27}}</ref> The book is listed at the [[bibliography]] of the Tanzania Development Trust,<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20141105001701/http://tanzdevtrust.org/bibliography ]</ref> on the reading list of various University courses<ref>{{cite web|url=http://liblists.derby.ac.uk/items/26FCD6C5-BE32-2BFA-92FF-C375A992B816.html |title=No man's land: an investigative journey through Kenya and Tanzania &#124; University of Derby |website=Liblists.derby.ac.uk |date= |accessdate=2016-10-27}}</ref> and as recommended reading by the [[Lonely Planet]] Kenya guide.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20101007212224/http://www.lonelyplanet.com/kenya/travel-tips-and-articles/75825 ]</ref>
==References== {{Reflist}}
