'''Professor Souleymane Faye''' is a [[Senegal]]ese professor of [[linguistics]] at the [[Cheikh Anta Diop University]] (CLAD),<ref>Professor Faye in Africorps {{cite web |url=http://www.africorp.org/whoweare.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2012-08-13 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120419010656/http://www.africorp.org/whoweare.html |archivedate=2012-04-19 |df= }} Retrieved 14 August 2012)</ref> current head of the Serer Division at the [[Centre de linguistique appliquée de Dakar]], author of [[Serer language|Serer]] and [[Cangin languages]]<ref>"Workshop Know Your Rights!/Connais Tes Droits!", report by African Commission on Human Rights, [[Brandeis University]] and the [[West Africa]]n Research Centre (WARC) (2007) [http://alma.matrix.msu.edu/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/KYR_final_report.pdf], pp 11 and 15</ref><ref name="Faye">{{fr}} Faye, Souleymane (CLAD, Dakar), & Dijkstra, Hillebrand ([[SIL International|Société Internationale de Linguistique]], Dakar), "GLOTTALISEES DU [[Serer language|SEREER-SIIN]], DU [[Saafi language|SAAFISAAFI]] ET DU [[Noon language|NOON]] DU [[Senegal|SENEGAL]] : ETUDE COMPARATIVE DE LA SONORITE", [http://rds.refer.sn/sites/www.sudlangues.sn/IMG/pdf-old/doc-96.pdf]</ref><ref name="Faye"/><ref>Some of Professor Faye's books / papers [in] [http://openlibrary.org/authors/OL315727A/Souleymane_Faye Open Library]</ref><ref>[http://clad.ucad.sn/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=27&Itemid=45 CLAD personnel] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140401061818/http://clad.ucad.sn/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=27&Itemid=45 |date=2014-04-01 }}</ref> and a [[journalist]].<ref>{{fr}} [[Inter Press Service]] (IPC), News Agency [http://www.ipsnews.net/author/souleymane-faye/]</ref> Himself [[Serer people|Serer]] from the [[Faye family]], he has authored and co-authored several books and papers in Serer, [[Wolof language|Wolof]], French and English.<ref name="Faye"/> As of 2015, Professor Faye is Head of Seereer and Cangin Languages at the Seereer Resource Centre.<ref>The Seereer Resource Centre : ''"The Team"'' [http://www.seereer.com/the-team]</ref>
